{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893326049,"sessionID":"ses_28486105affee2QiTZn90dNmET","part":{"id":"prt_d7b79ffdd001NEDwtRlD59CgIW","messageID":"msg_d7b79f08f001R8phtLIIxM3Heo","sessionID":"ses_28486105affee2QiTZn90dNmET","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_6292263acc7647ed95d317c5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure - find all directories and key files\n2. Look for any existing AR-040 or ST-3 related files, specs, or documentation\n3. Find the sdk-python directory and its tests directory structure\n4. Look for any existing tasks.md or checklist files as examples\n5. Find any design documents, specs, or requirements related to Python SDK/CLI testing\n6. Look for Stage ST-3 completion artifacts or documentation\n7. Understand what the Python SDK does - find the main source files, modules, classes, functions\n8. Check for any existing test files in sdk-python/tests to understand what's already tested vs what needs testing\n9. Look for any CLI-related code in the Python SDK\n\nSearch broadly across the entire workspace. Return a comprehensive summary of:\n- Project structure overview\n- What AR-040 and ST-3 refer to (find any related docs)\n- Full sdk-python directory tree\n- Existing test coverage in sdk-python/tests\n- What the Python SDK/CLI provides (modules, features, entry points)\n- Any spec or design documents related to this work","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28485dac6ffeb6cRGXRY17Ry24 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the entire project. Here is the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Summary\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\n**AgentCube** is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents. The workspace root is:\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n```\n\n**Top-level directories:**\n```\nagentd/                    # Idle cleanup controller (Go)\nbin/                       # Binary utilities\nchanges/                   # AR-001 through AR-040 (change request directories)\nci-cd/                     # CI/CD design and spec\ncli-toolkit/               # Python CLI toolkit\nclient-go/                 # Go Kubernetes client\ncmd/                       # CLI entry points (Go)\ncode-execution/            # Code execution design/spec\ndeployment/                # Deployment configurations\ndesign.md                  # AR-040 Design document\ndelta-spec.md              # AR-038 Delta Spec (Go workloadmanager tests)\ndocker/                    # Docker configurations\nexample/                   # Example applications (e.g., PCAP Analyzer)\ngithub/                    # GitHub Actions workflows\nhack/                      # Code generation scripts\nidle-cleanup/              # Idle cleanup design/spec\nintegrations/              # Dify plugin integration\nmanifests/                 # Kubernetes manifests\npkg/                       # Go packages (apis, agentd, picod, store, workloadmanager)\nproject.md                 # Project context document\nproposal.md                # AR-036 proposal (Dify plugin)\npython-sdk/                # Python SDK (agentcube-sdk) -- KEY DIRECTORY\nsandbox-orchestration/     # Sandbox orchestration design/spec\nsession-routing/           # Session routing design/spec\nsession-store/             # Session store design/spec\ntasks.md                   # AR-023 tasks (CLI invoke/status commands)\ntest_spec.md               # Test specification\ntest/                      # Go test scripts\ntesting/                   # Testing utilities\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. What AR-040 and ST-3 Refer To\n\n**AR-040** = \"Python SDK/CLI Testing\" -- This is the current active change request. It is about building comprehensive unit tests for the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`).\n\n**ST-3** = \"Stage 3: Design Complete\" -- This is a project lifecycle stage. All AR tasks files state `Precondition: Stage ST-3 (Design) completed`, meaning the design phase must be finished before implementation tasks begin.\n\n**AR-040 directory contents:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/proposal.md` -- Full proposal (211 lines) describing scope, architecture, test strategy, acceptance criteria\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/design.md` -- Design document (86 lines, mostly TODO templates)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md` -- Delta spec (364 lines) with 14 requirements (R-1 through R-14) identifying test coverage gaps\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/tasks.md` -- Tasks file (44 lines, mostly TODO placeholders)\n\n**Root-level AR-040 documents** (duplicates/supersets):\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` -- 618 lines, very detailed design with full test plans, bug fixes, new test specifications\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` -- 826 lines, actually AR-038 (Go workloadmanager tests), NOT AR-040\n\n---\n\n### 3. Full sdk-python (python-sdk) Directory Tree\n\n```\npython-sdk/\n├── pyproject.toml                          # Package: agentcube-sdk v0.1.0, Python >=3.9\n├── spec.md                                 # SDK specification (133 lines)\n├── design.md                               # SDK design document (314 lines)\n├── .pytest_cache/                          # Pytest cache\n├── agentcube_sdk.egg-info/                 # Egg info\n├── agentcube/                              # SDK source package\n│   ├── __init__.py                         # Exports: CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n│   ├── code_interpreter.py                 # CodeInterpreterClient (161 lines)\n│   ├── agent_runtime.py                    # AgentRuntimeClient (79 lines)\n│   ├── exceptions.py                       # Exception hierarchy (21 lines)\n│   ├── clients/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                     # Re-exports: ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n│   │   ├── control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient (96 lines)\n│   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (176 lines)\n│   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (80 lines)\n│   └── utils/\n│       ├── __init__.py                     # Empty module marker\n│       ├── http.py                         # create_session() with HTTPAdapter (14 lines)\n│       ├── utils.py                        # read_token_from_file() (7 lines)\n│       └── log.py                          # get_logger() (17 lines)\n└── tests/                                  # Test package\n    ├── __init__.py                         # Package marker\n    ├── conftest.py                         # pytest fixtures (14 lines)\n    ├── test_imports.py                     # Package import/export tests (55 lines)\n    ├── test_exceptions.py                  # Exception hierarchy tests (77 lines)\n    ├── test_utils.py                       # Utility function tests (93 lines)\n    ├── test_control_plane.py               # ControlPlaneClient tests (370 lines)\n    ├── test_data_plane.py                  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient tests (641 lines)\n    ├── test_code_interpreter.py            # CodeInterpreterClient tests (635 lines)\n    └── test_agent_runtime.py               # AgentRuntime* tests (837 lines)\n```\n\n**Total SDK source code: ~650 lines across 12 files.**\n**Total existing test code: ~2,708 lines across 7 test files.**\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing Test Coverage in python-sdk/tests\n\n| Test File | Lines | Coverage Status |\n|-----------|-------|-----------------|\n| `test_imports.py` | 55 | **Good** -- tests all imports and `__all__` exports |\n| `test_exceptions.py` | 77 | **Good** -- full exception hierarchy, attributes, messages |\n| `test_utils.py` | 93 | **Partial** -- missing edge cases for `read_token_from_file` (empty file, multiline), `get_logger` (handler dedup, formatter, handler type), `create_session` (independent instances) |\n| `test_control_plane.py` | 370 | **Good** -- init, URL resolution, auth token, create_session, delete_session, close, session reuse |\n| `test_data_plane.py` | 641 | **Good** -- init, base URL, _request, execute_command, run_code, write_file, upload_file, download_file, list_files, close |\n| `test_code_interpreter.py` | 635 | **Partial** -- has a BUG: 3 methods in `TestStop` class are missing `test_` prefix (`stop_closes_dp_client`, `stop_deletes_session`, `stop_closes_cp_client`) and will NOT be discovered by pytest |\n| `test_agent_runtime.py` | 837 | **Good** -- data plane client, bootstrap, invoke, high-level client init, session, context manager, invoke, close, integration |\n\n**Missing test file:** `test_integration.py` -- The design document calls for a NEW cross-component integration test file with 20 test cases.\n\n**Key gaps identified in delta-spec.md:**\n1. Data plane init failure recovery -- **Missing**\n2. Execute command timeout buffer (+2.0s) -- **Missing** (though data_plane.py tests it)\n3. SA token file fallback -- **Missing**\n4. run_code write-file-then-execute flow -- **Partial** (mocks delegation only)\n5. Context manager exception propagation -- **Missing**\n6. Invoke per-request header isolation -- **Partial**\n7. Multipart upload Content-Type absence -- **Missing**\n8. Download path leading slash stripping -- **Missing**\n9. Delete session 404 idempotency -- **Covered**\n10. Invoke response parsing -- **Covered**\n11. Package `__all__` exports -- **Covered** (in test_imports.py)\n12. Create session URL/body contract -- **Partial**\n13. write_file base64 encoding -- **Covered**\n14. Bootstrap session ID missing header -- **Covered**\n\n---\n\n### 5. What the Python SDK/CLI Provides\n\nThe SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) is a **Python client library** (NOT a CLI tool) with no CLI entry points. It provides:\n\n#### High-Level Clients (Public API via `agentcube.__all__`):\n\n1. **`CodeInterpreterClient`** (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`, 161 lines)\n   - High-level facade for Code Interpreter sessions\n   - Manages session lifecycle (create/reuse via ControlPlaneClient)\n   - Executes code and manages files via data plane\n   - Context manager support (`__enter__`/`__exit__`)\n   - Methods: `execute_command()`, `run_code()`, `write_file()`, `upload_file()`, `download_file()`, `list_files()`, `stop()`\n\n2. **`AgentRuntimeClient`** (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`, 79 lines)\n   - High-level facade for Agent Runtime invocation\n   - Bootstraps sessions from Router endpoint\n   - Context manager support\n   - Methods: `invoke()`, `close()`\n\n#### Low-Level Clients (Internal, via `agentcube.clients.__all__`):\n\n3. **`ControlPlaneClient`** (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`, 96 lines)\n   - Workload Manager API client\n   - Creates/deletes code interpreter sessions\n   - Auth via token arg or K8s ServiceAccount file\n   - Methods: `create_session()`, `delete_session()`, `close()`\n\n4. **`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`** (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`, 176 lines)\n   - Router data plane client for Code Interpreter\n   - Command execution, file operations\n   - Timeout buffer logic (+2.0s)\n   - Methods: `execute_command()`, `run_code()`, `write_file()`, `upload_file()`, `download_file()`, `list_files()`, `close()`\n\n5. **`AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`** (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`, 80 lines)\n   - Router data plane client for Agent Runtime\n   - Session bootstrap, invocation\n   - Methods: `bootstrap_session_id()`, `invoke()`, `close()`\n\n#### Exceptions (`agentcube/exceptions.py`, 21 lines):\n- `AgentCubeError` (base)\n- `CommandExecutionError` (with `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command` attributes)\n- `SessionError` (docstring only, not raised)\n- `DataPlaneError` (docstring only, not raised)\n\n#### Utilities:\n- `create_session()` -- Creates requests.Session with HTTPAdapter pooling\n- `read_token_from_file()` -- Reads K8s SA token, strips whitespace\n- `get_logger()` -- Creates/reuses named loggers with StreamHandler\n\n#### No CLI code exists in python-sdk\nThe package has no CLI entry points, no `__main__.py`, no Typer/click/argparse usage. The CLI toolkit exists separately at `cli-toolkit/` and `cmd/cli/`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Spec and Design Documents\n\n| Document | Path | Lines | Purpose |\n|----------|------|-------|---------|\n| **SDK Spec** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/spec.md` | 133 | SDK requirements and scenarios |\n| **SDK Design** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/design.md` | 314 | SDK architecture, class signatures, HTTP contracts |\n| **AR-040 Design** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` | 618 | Detailed test plan, bug fixes, new tests, coverage targets |\n| **AR-040 Proposal** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/proposal.md` | 211 | Scope, architecture, acceptance criteria |\n| **AR-040 Delta Spec** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md` | 364 | 14 requirements, gap analysis, file structure |\n| **AR-040 Tasks** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/tasks.md` | 44 | Task checklist (mostly TODO) |\n| **Project Context** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md` | 45 | Architecture overview, tech stack |\n| **SDD Prompt** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md` | 465 | SDK spec + design combined (reference doc) |\n\n---\n\n### 7. Key Findings for AR-040 Implementation\n\n**Bug to fix:**\n- `test_code_interpreter.py` lines 288, 305, 322: Three test methods in `TestStop` class are named `stop_closes_dp_client`, `stop_deletes_session`, `stop_closes_cp_client` -- missing `test_` prefix, so pytest does not discover them.\n\n**New file needed:**\n- `tests/test_integration.py` -- 20 cross-component integration tests (documented in design.md section 5.3)\n\n**Existing tests to extend:**\n- `test_code_interpreter.py` -- 13 additional tests planned (stop edge cases, run_code language variants, execute_command edge cases, init flags)\n- `test_data_plane.py` -- 10 additional tests (HTTP error propagation, unicode, download file creation, _request timeout)\n- `test_control_plane.py` -- 5 additional tests (none metadata, trailing slash, URL construction, empty token)\n- `test_agent_runtime.py` -- 4 additional tests (HTTP error, empty payload, empty header string, close delegation)\n- `test_utils.py` -- 6 additional tests (empty file, multiline token, handler dedup, formatter, handler type, independent sessions)\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28485dac6ffeb6cRGXRY17Ry24","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775893095734,"end":1775893326046}}}}
