{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893340980,"sessionID":"ses_28486105affee2QiTZn90dNmET","part":{"id":"prt_d7b7ddf3e0010U2t8qE6n3SyEB","messageID":"msg_d7b7dcd3a001XqvQznwJGlah1g","sessionID":"ses_28486105affee2QiTZn90dNmET","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_072548e7068c4b6f8662b709","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 单元测试 — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This AR covers comprehensive Python unit tests for the `agentcube-sdk` package (`sdk-python/`). The SDK provides high-level Python clients for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 Scope\n10: \n11: | Module | File | Lines | Test File | Status |\n12: |--------|------|-------|-----------|--------|\n13: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` | 161 | `tests/test_code_interpreter.py` | **Partial** — 635 lines, but 3 methods missing `test_` prefix (won't run) |\n14: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` | 79 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** — 837 lines |\n15: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` | 96 | `tests/test_control_plane.py` | **Good** — 370 lines |\n16: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | 176 | `tests/test_data_plane.py` | **Good** — 641 lines |\n17: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | 80 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** |\n18: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes | 21 | `tests/test_exceptions.py` | **Good** — 77 lines |\n19: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` | 14 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Good** |\n20: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` | 7 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Partial** — missing edge cases |\n21: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` | 17 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Partial** — missing handler reuse test |\n22: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports | 5 | `tests/test_imports.py` | **Good** — 55 lines |\n23: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Client re-exports | 6 | `tests/test_imports.py` | **Good** |\n24: \n25: ### 1.3 System Context\n26: \n27: ```\n28: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n29: │                        Python SDK (agentcube)                        │\n30: │                                                                       │\n31: │  ┌──────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     │\n32: │  │  CodeInterpreterClient│     │     AgentRuntimeClient        │     │\n33: │  │  (high-level facade)  │     │   (high-level facade)         │     │\n34: │  └───────┬──────────────┘     └──────────┬────────────────────┘     │\n35: │          │                               │                           │\n36: │  ┌───────▼──────────────┐     ┌──────────▼────────────────────┐     │\n37: │  │  ControlPlaneClient  │     │  AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient  │     │\n38: │  │  (Workload Manager)  │     │   (Router — Agent Runtime)    │     │\n39: │  └──────────────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     │\n40: │          │                                                       │\n41: │  ┌───────▼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n42: │  │           CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient                      │  │\n43: │  │              (Router — Code Interpreter)                      │  │\n44: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n45: │                                                                       │\n46: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n47: │  │                    Utilities                                   │  │\n48: │  │  create_session  │  read_token_from_file  │  get_logger       │  │\n49: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n50: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n51: │  │                   Exceptions                                   │  │\n52: │  │  AgentCubeError → CommandExecutionError                       │  │\n53: │  │                 → SessionError                                │  │\n54: │  │                 → DataPlaneError                              │  │\n55: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n56: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n57:          │                                              │\n58:          ▼                                              ▼\n59: ┌──────────────────┐                        ┌──────────────────────┐\n60: │  Workload Manager│                        │      Router           │\n61: │  (Control Plane) │                        │  (Data Plane)         │\n62: │  K8s API Server  │                        │  HTTP proxy to pods   │\n63: └──────────────────┘                        └──────────────────────┘\n64: ```\n65: \n66: ### 1.4 Design Principles\n67: \n68: - **Mock at the boundary**: All HTTP calls are mocked via `MagicMock` on `session.post/get/delete/request`. No real network calls.\n69: - **`unittest.mock.patch`**: Used for class-level and function-level patching. Consistent with existing test patterns.\n70: - **Environment isolation**: Tests that depend on env vars use `patch.dict(os.environ, ...)` with `clear=True`.\n71: - **Resource cleanup**: Every test that creates a client calls `client.close()` or `client.stop()` to release HTTP sessions.\n72: - **Table-driven patterns**: Where applicable (e.g., language aliases, timeout variants), use parameterized approaches.\n73: \n74: ### 1.5 Package Structure (test files)\n75: \n76: ```\n77: python-sdk/tests/\n78: ├── __init__.py                          # Package marker\n79: ├── conftest.py                          # Shared fixtures (mock_requests_session, mock_create_session)\n80: ├── test_imports.py                      # Package import and __all__ verification\n81: ├── test_exceptions.py                   # Exception hierarchy tests\n82: ├── test_utils.py                        # Utility function tests (http, utils, log)\n83: ├── test_control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient tests\n84: ├── test_data_plane.py                   # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient tests\n85: ├── test_code_interpreter.py             # CodeInterpreterClient tests\n86: ├── test_agent_runtime.py                # AgentRuntimeClient + AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient tests\n87: └── test_integration.py                  # NEW — cross-component integration tests\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### 1.6 Dependencies\n91: \n92: | Dependency | Version | Test Use |\n93: |------------|---------|----------|\n94: | `pytest` | ≥8.0 | Test runner, fixtures, parametrize |\n95: | `requests` | any | HTTP client (mocked) |\n96: | `PyJWT` | ≥2.0.0 | SDK dependency (not directly tested) |\n97: | `cryptography` | any | SDK dependency (not directly tested) |\n98: | `unittest.mock` | stdlib | MagicMock, patch, patch.dict |\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## 2. Data Structures\n103: \n104: ### 2.1 Mock Objects Required\n105: \n106: #### `mock_http_response` (requests.Response)\n107: \n108: Standard mock for HTTP responses across all client tests:\n109: \n110: ```python\n111: mock_resp = MagicMock(spec=requests.Response)\n112: mock_resp.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"abc-123\"}\n113: mock_resp.status_code = 200\n114: mock_resp.raise_for_status = MagicMock()\n115: mock_resp.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-1\"}\n116: mock_resp.iter_content.return_value = [b\"chunk1\", b\"chunk2\"]\n117: ```\n118: \n119: #### `mock_session` (requests.Session)\n120: \n121: Used when testing session-level behavior:\n122: \n123: ```python\n124: mock_session = MagicMock()\n125: mock_session.post.return_value = mock_resp\n126: mock_session.get.return_value = mock_resp\n127: mock_session.delete.return_value = mock_resp\n128: mock_session.request.return_value = mock_resp\n129: mock_session.headers = {}\n130: mock_session.adapters = {\"http://\": adapter, \"https://\": adapter}\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ### 2.2 Test Fixtures\n134: \n135: #### CodeInterpreterClient fixture\n136: \n137: ```python\n138: def make_ci_client(session_id=\"sess-1\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\", **kwargs):\n139:     \"\"\"Create a CodeInterpreterClient with mocked dependencies.\"\"\"\n140:     with patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.ControlPlaneClient\") as mock_cp, \\\n141:          patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n142:         mock_cp.return_value = MagicMock()\n143:         mock_dp.return_value = MagicMock()\n144:         client = CodeInterpreterClient(session_id=session_id, router_url=router_url, **kwargs)\n145:         yield client, mock_cp, mock_dp\n146:         client.stop()\n147: ```\n148: \n149: #### AgentRuntimeClient fixture\n150: \n151: ```python\n152: def make_ar_client(session_id=\"sess-1\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\", **kwargs):\n153:     \"\"\"Create an AgentRuntimeClient with mocked dependencies.\"\"\"\n154:     with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n155:         mock_dp.return_value = MagicMock()\n156:         mock_dp.return_value.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = session_id\n157:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=router_url, **kwargs)\n158:         yield client, mock_dp\n159:         client.close()\n160: ```\n161: \n162: ### 2.2 Key Class Signatures\n163: \n164: #### CodeInterpreterClient\n165: \n166: | Method | Signature | Delegates To |\n167: |--------|-----------|-------------|\n168: | `__init__` | `(name, namespace, ttl, workload_manager_url, router_url, auth_token, verbose, session_id)` | ControlPlaneClient + CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient |\n169: | `_init_data_plane` | `() -> None` | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name) |\n170: | `__enter__` | `() -> self` | — |\n171: | `__exit__` | `(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None` | `stop()` |\n172: | `stop` | `() -> None` | dp_client.close(), cp_client.delete_session(), cp_client.close() |\n173: | `execute_command` | `(command: str, timeout: Optional[float]) -> str` | dp_client.execute_command([command], timeout+2.0) |\n174: | `run_code` | `(language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float]) -> str` | write_file() + execute_command() |\n175: | `write_file` | `(content: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | dp_client.write_file() |\n176: | `upload_file` | `(local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | dp_client.upload_file() |\n177: | `download_file` | `(remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None` | dp_client.download_file() |\n178: | `list_files` | `(path: str=\".\") -> Any` | dp_client.list_files() |\n179: \n180: #### ControlPlaneClient\n181: \n182: | Method | Signature | HTTP |\n183: |--------|-----------|------|\n184: | `__init__` | `(workload_manager_url, auth_token, timeout, connect_timeout, pool_connections, pool_maxsize)` | Creates session with headers |\n185: | `create_session` | `(name, namespace, metadata, ttl) -> str` | POST `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` |\n186: | `delete_session` | `(session_id: str) -> bool` | DELETE `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}` |\n187: | `close` | `() -> None` | session.close() |\n188: \n189: #### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n190: \n191: | Method | Signature | HTTP |\n192: |--------|-----------|------|\n193: | `__init__` | `(session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name, base_url, timeout, connect_timeout, pool_connections, pool_maxsize)` | Creates session with `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n194: | `_request` | `(method, endpoint, body, **kwargs) -> Response` | `{base_url}{endpoint}` |\n195: | `execute_command` | `(command: Union[str, List], timeout: Optional[float]) -> str` | POST `api/execute` |\n196: | `run_code` | `(language, code, timeout) -> str` | write_file + execute_command |\n197: | `write_file` | `(content, remote_path) -> None` | POST `api/files` (JSON, base64) |\n198: | `upload_file` | `(local_path, remote_path) -> None` | POST `api/files` (multipart) |\n199: | `download_file` | `(remote_path, local_path) -> None` | GET `api/files/{clean_path}` (stream) |\n200: | `list_files` | `(path=\".\") -> Any` | GET `api/files?path={path}` |\n201: | `close` | `() -> None` | session.close() |\n202: \n203: #### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n204: \n205: | Method | Signature | HTTP |\n206: |--------|-----------|------|\n207: | `__init__` | `(router_url, namespace, agent_name, timeout, connect_timeout, pool_connections, pool_maxsize)` | Creates session |\n208: | `bootstrap_session_id` | `() -> str` | GET `{base_url}` → reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n209: | `invoke` | `(session_id, payload, timeout) -> Response` | POST `{base_url}` with JSON + session header |\n210: | `close` | `() -> None` | session.close() |\n211: \n212: #### AgentRuntimeClient\n213: \n214: | Method | Signature | Delegates To |\n215: |--------|-----------|-------------|\n216: | `__init__` | `(agent_name, namespace, router_url, verbose, session_id, timeout, connect_timeout)` | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient + bootstrap |\n217: | `__enter__` | `() -> self` | — |\n218: | `__exit__` | `(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None` | `close()` |\n219: | `invoke` | `(payload: Dict, timeout: Optional[float]) -> Any` | dp_client.invoke() → resp.json() |\n220: | `close` | `() -> None` | dp_client.close() |\n221: \n222: ---\n223: \n224: ## 3. API Contracts\n225: \n226: ### 3.1 CodeInterpreterClient Contracts\n227: \n228: #### Initialization\n229: \n230: | Scenario | Condition | Result |\n231: |----------|-----------|--------|\n232: | No session_id provided | `session_id=None` | Calls `cp_client.create_session()`, sets `self.session_id`, sets `_session_created=True` |\n233: | Session_id provided | `session_id=\"existing\"` | Skips create_session, sets `_session_created=False` |\n234: | Router URL from arg | `router_url=\"http://x\"` | Uses provided URL |\n235: | Router URL from env | `router_url=None`, `ROUTER_URL=\"http://x\"` | Uses env var |\n236: | Router URL missing | Neither arg nor env | Raises `ValueError(\"router_url must be provided or ROUTER_URL env var must be set\")` |\n237: \n238: #### Data Plane Init Failure\n239: \n240: | Scenario | `_session_created` | `session_id` | Result |\n241: |----------|-------------------|-------------|--------|\n242: | DP init fails, session was created | True | non-None | Logs warning, calls `delete_session(session_id)`, sets `session_id=None`, re-raises |\n243: | DP init fails, session was reused | False | non-None | Re-raises without cleanup (caller owns session) |\n244: \n245: #### Context Manager\n246: \n247: | Scenario | Result |\n248: |----------|--------|\n249: | `__enter__` | Returns `self` |\n250: | `__exit__` (no exception) | Calls `stop()` |\n251: | `__exit__` (with exception) | Calls `stop()`, returns `None` (does not suppress) |\n252: \n253: #### stop()\n254: \n255: | Condition | Action |\n256: |-----------|--------|\n257: | `dp_client` exists and not None | `dp_client.close()`, set to `None` |\n258: | `session_id` is not None | `cp_client.delete_session(session_id)`, set to `None` |\n259: | `cp_client` exists and not None | `cp_client.close()`, set to `None` |\n260: | Called multiple times | Idempotent — no-op after first call |\n261: \n262: #### execute_command\n263: \n264: | Input | Transformation | DP Call |\n265: |-------|---------------|---------|\n266: | `\"echo hello\"` (string) | → `[\"echo hello\"]` | `dp.execute_command([\"echo hello\"], timeout=read_timeout)` |\n267: | `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (list) | → `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (as-is) | `dp.execute_command([\"ls\", \"-la\"], timeout=read_timeout)` |\n268: | `timeout=None` | → `timeout_value=120`, `read_timeout=122.0` | DP call with `(connect_timeout, 122.0)` |\n269: | `timeout=10.0` | → `timeout_value=10.0`, `read_timeout=12.0` | DP call with `(connect_timeout, 12.0)` |\n270: \n271: #### run_code\n272: \n273: | Language | Action |\n274: |----------|--------|\n275: | `\"python\"`, `\"py\"`, `\"python3\"` (case-insensitive) | Write timestamped `.py` file, execute `python3 <file>` |\n276: | Any other | Raises `ValueError(\"Unsupported language: {language}\")` |\n277: \n278: ### 3.2 ControlPlaneClient Contracts\n279: \n280: #### Initialization\n281: \n282: | Condition | Result |\n283: |-----------|--------|\n284: | `workload_manager_url` provided | `base_url = workload_manager_url` |\n285: | `workload_manager_url=None`, env set | `base_url = WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` |\n286: | Neither provided | Raises `ValueError(\"workload_manager_url must be provided or WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var must be set\")` |\n287: | `auth_token` provided | `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header set |\n288: | `auth_token=None`, SA file exists | Token read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n289: | `auth_token=None`, SA file missing | No Authorization header set |\n290: | `auth_token=\"\"` (empty string) | No Authorization header set (falsy check) |\n291: \n292: #### create_session\n293: \n294: | HTTP | Request | Response |\n295: |------|---------|----------|\n296: | POST `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON: `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` | Returns `data[\"sessionId\"]` |\n297: | Timeout | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` | — |\n298: | Missing sessionId in response | — | Raises `ValueError(\"Response missing 'sessionId' field\")` |\n299: | HTTP error | — | `resp.raise_for_status()` propagates |\n300: \n301: #### delete_session\n302: \n303: | HTTP Status | Result |\n304: |-------------|--------|\n305: | 2xx | Returns `True` |\n306: | 404 | Returns `True` (idempotent) |\n307: | Other error (HTTPError, ConnectionError, Timeout) | Logs warning, returns `False` |\n308: \n309: ### 3.3 CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Contracts\n310: \n311: #### Base URL Construction\n312: \n313: | Condition | Result |\n314: |-----------|--------|\n315: | `base_url` provided | `self.base_url = base_url` (ignores router_url/namespace/cr_name) |\n316: | `base_url=None` | `self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` |\n317: \n318: #### execute_command\n319: \n320: | Input | Body | Timeout |\n321: |-------|------|---------|\n322: | `\"sleep 10\"`, `timeout=10.0` | `{\"command\": [\"sleep\", \"10\"], \"timeout\": \"10s\"}` | `(connect_timeout, 12.0)` |\n323: | `\"ls\"`, `timeout=None` | `{\"command\": [\"ls\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` | `(connect_timeout, 122.0)` |\n324: | `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (list) | `{\"command\": [\"ls\", \"-la\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` | `(connect_timeout, 122.0)` |\n325: \n326: | Response | Result |\n327: |----------|--------|\n328: | `{\"exit_code\": 0, \"stdout\": \"ok\"}` | Returns `\"ok\"` |\n329: | `{\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"err\"}` | Raises `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"err\", command=[...])` |\n330: \n331: #### write_file\n332: \n333: | Input | Body |\n334: |-------|------|\n335: | `\"hello\"`, `/tmp/test.txt` | `{\"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"content\": base64(\"hello\"), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n336: \n337: #### upload_file\n338: \n339: | Input | Multipart |\n340: |-------|-----------|\n341: | `/local/file.txt`, `/remote/file.txt` | `files={'file': ('file.txt', f)}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, headers include `x-agentcube-session-id` |\n342: \n343: #### download_file\n344: \n345: | Input | URL |\n346: |-------|-----|\n347: | `/remote/path.txt`, `/local/out.txt` | GET `{base_url}api/files/remote/path.txt` (leading `/` stripped) |\n348: \n349: ### 3.4 AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Contracts\n350: \n351: #### bootstrap_session_id\n352: \n353: | Response Header | Result |\n354: |-----------------|--------|\n355: | `x-agentcube-session-id: abc-123` | Returns `\"abc-123\"` |\n356: | Missing header | Raises `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` |\n357: | HTTP error | `raise_for_status()` propagates |\n358: \n359: #### invoke\n360: \n361: | Input | Headers | Timeout |\n362: |-------|---------|---------|\n363: | `session_id=\"s1\"`, `payload={}`, `timeout=None` | `{\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"s1\", \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}` | `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` |\n364: | `timeout=30.0` | Same | `(connect_timeout, 30.0)` |\n365: \n366: ### 3.5 Utility Contracts\n367: \n368: #### create_session\n369: \n370: | Input | Result |\n371: |-------|--------|\n372: | `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` (defaults) | Session with HTTPAdapter mounted on `http://` and `https://` |\n373: | Custom values | Session with custom pool settings |\n374: \n375: #### read_token_from_file\n376: \n377: | Condition | Result |\n378: |-----------|--------|\n379: | File exists with `\"token\\n\"` | Returns `\"token\"` (stripped) |\n380: | File exists with `\"  token  \\n\"` | Returns `\"token\"` (stripped) |\n381: | File not found | Returns `\"\"` |\n382: \n383: #### get_logger\n384: \n385: | Condition | Result |\n386: |-----------|--------|\n387: | First call with name `\"x\"` | Creates logger, adds StreamHandler with formatter |\n388: | Second call with same name `\"x\"` | Returns existing logger (no duplicate handlers) |\n389: | `level=logging.DEBUG` | Logger level = 10 |\n390: | `level=\"DEBUG\"` | Logger level = 10 |\n391: | `level=logging.INFO` (default) | Logger level = 20 |\n392: \n393: ---\n394: \n395: ## 4. Error Handling\n396: \n397: ### 4.1 Error Classification\n398: \n399: | Component | Error Source | Test Strategy |\n400: |-----------|-------------|---------------|\n401: | ControlPlaneClient | `create_session` HTTP error | Mock `session.post` with `raise_for_status` side_effect |\n402: | ControlPlaneClient | `delete_session` network error | Mock `session.delete` with `RequestException` side_effect |\n403: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | `execute_command` non-zero exit | Mock response JSON with `exit_code != 0` |\n404: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | Any HTTP error | Mock `session.request` with `raise_for_status` side_effect |\n405: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `bootstrap_session_id` missing header | Mock response with empty headers dict |\n406: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `invoke` HTTP error | Mock `session.post` with `raise_for_status` side_effect |\n407: | CodeInterpreterClient | DP init failure | Mock `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` constructor to raise |\n408: | CodeInterpreterClient | Router URL missing | Patch env, assert `ValueError` |\n409: | AgentRuntimeClient | Session not initialized | Mock bootstrap to return `None` or `\"\"` |\n410: \n411: ### 4.2 Exception Hierarchy\n412: \n413: ```\n414: Exception\n415: └── AgentCubeError (base)\n416:     ├── CommandExecutionError (exit_code, stderr, command)\n417:     ├── SessionError (docstring only, not raised by core)\n418:     └── DataPlaneError (docstring only, not raised by core)\n419: ```\n420: \n421: Tests verify:\n422: - `issubclass(CommandExecutionError, AgentCubeError)` → True\n423: - `issubclass(SessionError, AgentCubeError)` → True\n424: - `issubclass(DataPlaneError, AgentCubeError)` → True\n425: - `CommandExecutionError` attributes: `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`\n426: - `CommandExecutionError` message format: `\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"`\n427: \n428: ---\n429: \n430: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n431: \n432: ### 5.1 Test Categories\n433: \n434: | Category | Scope | Files |\n435: |----------|-------|-------|\n436: | Import/export tests | Package structure, `__all__` | `test_imports.py` |\n437: | Exception tests | Hierarchy, attributes, messages | `test_exceptions.py` |\n438: | Utility tests | Pure functions, no side effects | `test_utils.py` |\n439: | Control plane tests | HTTP client, session lifecycle | `test_control_plane.py` |\n440: | Data plane tests (CI) | HTTP client, file ops, execute | `test_data_plane.py` |\n441: | Data plane tests (AR) | HTTP client, bootstrap, invoke | `test_agent_runtime.py` |\n442: | High-level CI client | Facade, lifecycle, delegation | `test_code_interpreter.py` |\n443: | High-level AR client | Facade, lifecycle, delegation | `test_agent_runtime.py` |\n444: | Integration tests | Cross-component, end-to-end flows | `test_integration.py` (NEW) |\n445: \n446: ### 5.2 Bug Fixes Required (Existing Tests)\n447: \n448: #### `test_code_interpreter.py` — Missing `test_` prefix\n449: \n450: Three methods in `TestStop` class are named without `test_` prefix and will NOT be discovered by pytest:\n451: \n452: | Current Name | Required Name |\n453: |--------------|---------------|\n454: | `stop_closes_dp_client` | `test_stop_closes_dp_client` |\n455: | `stop_deletes_session` | `test_stop_deletes_session` |\n456: | `stop_closes_cp_client` | `test_stop_closes_cp_client` |\n457: \n458: ### 5.3 Detailed Test Plan — New/Additional Tests\n459: \n460: #### `test_code_interpreter.py` — Additional Tests\n461: \n462: | # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n463: |---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n464: | 1 | `test_stop_when_session_id_is_none` | stop | session_id=None → skips delete_session, still closes dp and cp |\n465: | 2 | `test_stop_when_dp_client_not_initialized` | stop | No dp_client attribute → no crash (hasattr check) |\n466: | 3 | `test_stop_when_cp_client_not_initialized` | stop | No cp_client attribute → no crash (hasattr check) |\n467: | 4 | `test_run_code_python3_language` | run_code | `\"python3\"` → writes file + executes |\n468: | 5 | `test_run_code_py_language` | run_code | `\"py\"` → writes file + executes |\n469: | 6 | `test_run_code_case_insensitive` | run_code | `\"PYTHON\"` → writes file + executes |\n470: | 7 | `test_run_code_passes_timeout_to_execute` | run_code | `timeout=30.0` → passed through to execute_command |\n471: | 8 | `test_execute_command_with_list_input` | execute_command | `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` → passed as-is to dp (not double-wrapped) |\n472: | 9 | `test_execute_command_empty_string` | execute_command | `\"\"` → `[\"\"]` sent to dp |\n473: | 10 | `test_session_created_flag_true_when_no_session_id` | __init__ | `_session_created=True` when session_id=None |\n474: | 11 | `test_session_created_flag_false_when_session_id_provided` | __init__ | `_session_created=False` when session_id provided |\n475: | 12 | `test_logger_name_is_correct` | __init__ | `logger.name == \"agentcube.code_interpreter\"` |\n476: | 13 | `test_data_plane_init_called_with_correct_params` | _init_data_plane | session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name passed correctly |\n477: \n478: #### `test_data_plane.py` — Additional Tests\n479: \n480: | # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n481: |---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n482: | 1 | `test_execute_command_http_error_propagates` | execute_command | HTTP 500 → raise_for_status propagates HTTPError |\n483: | 2 | `test_write_file_http_error_propagates` | write_file | HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates |\n484: | 3 | `test_write_file_unicode_content` | write_file | Unicode string → base64 encoded correctly |\n485: | 4 | `test_upload_file_nonexistent_raises_io_error` | upload_file | File not found → FileNotFoundError propagates |\n486: | 5 | `test_upload_file_http_error_propagates` | upload_file | HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates |\n487: | 6 | `test_download_file_creates_local_file` | download_file | Verifies file content written correctly |\n488: | 7 | `test_list_files_http_error_propagates` | list_files | HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates |\n489: | 8 | `test_run_code_delegates_to_write_and_execute` | run_code | Full delegation path verified |\n490: | 9 | `test_request_default_timeout_tuple` | _request | No timeout override → `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` |\n491: | 10 | `test_request_custom_timeout_override` | _request | timeout kwarg → used instead of default |\n492: \n493: #### `test_control_plane.py` — Additional Tests\n494: \n495: | # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n496: |---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n497: | 1 | `test_create_session_with_none_metadata` | create_session | `metadata=None` → body includes `\"metadata\": null` |\n498: | 2 | `test_create_session_url_with_trailing_slash` | create_session | base_url with trailing slash → URL constructed correctly |\n499: | 3 | `test_delete_session_url_construction` | delete_session | Verifies exact URL format |\n500: | 4 | `test_session_headers_content_type_always_set` | __init__ | Content-Type always `application/json` |\n501: | 5 | `test_auth_token_empty_string_no_header` | __init__ | `auth_token=\"\"` → no Authorization header |\n502: \n503: #### `test_agent_runtime.py` — Additional Tests\n504: \n505: | # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n506: |---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n507: | 1 | `test_invoke_http_error_propagates` | invoke (DP) | HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates |\n508: | 2 | `test_invoke_with_empty_payload` | invoke (DP) | `{}` → valid POST |\n509: | 3 | `test_bootstrap_session_id_empty_string_treated_as_missing` | bootstrap_session_id | Header value `\"\"` → raises ValueError |\n510: | 4 | `test_close_delegates_to_session_close` | close (DP) | Verifies session.close() called |\n511: \n512: #### `test_utils.py` — Additional Tests\n513: \n514: | # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n515: |---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n516: | 1 | `test_read_token_from_file_empty_file` | read_token_from_file | Empty file → returns `\"\"` |\n517: | 2 | `test_read_token_from_file_multiline_strips` | read_token_from_file | `\"token\\n\\n\"` → returns `\"token\"` |\n518: | 3 | `test_get_logger_handler_not_duplicated` | get_logger | Second call with same name → only 1 handler |\n519: | 4 | `test_get_logger_formatter_is_set` | get_logger | Handler has Formatter with correct format string |\n520: | 5 | `test_get_logger_handler_is_stream_handler` | get_logger | Handler type is StreamHandler |\n521: | 6 | `test_create_session_independent_instances` | create_session | Two calls → two independent Session objects |\n522: \n523: #### `test_integration.py` — NEW File\n524: \n525: | # | Test Name | Components | Description |\n526: |---|-----------|------------|-------------|\n527: | 1 | `test_ci_full_lifecycle_create_execute_stop` | CI Client + CP + DP | Create session → execute command → stop (full flow with all mocks) |\n528: | 2 | `test_ci_context_manager_with_exception` | CI Client + CP + DP | Exception in context block → stop still called |\n529: | 3 | `test_ci_pre_provisioned_session_no_control_plane_calls` | CI Client + CP | session_id provided → no create_session call |\n530: | 4 | `test_ci_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup` | CI Client + CP + DP | DP init fails → session deleted, exception re-raised |\n531: | 5 | `test_ar_full_lifecycle_bootstrap_invoke_close` | AR Client + DP | Bootstrap session → invoke → close (full flow) |\n532: | 6 | `test_ar_context_manager_with_exception` | AR Client + DP | Exception in context block → close still called |\n533: | 7 | `test_ar_pre_provisioned_session_no_bootstrap` | AR Client + DP | session_id provided → no bootstrap call |\n534: | 8 | `test_ar_missing_session_id_invoke_raises` | AR Client + DP | Bootstrap returns None → invoke raises ValueError |\n535: | 9 | `test_ci_execute_command_timeout_propagation` | CI Client + DP | Custom timeout → +2.0 buffer → DP receives correct value |\n536: | 10 | `test_ar_invoke_timeout_propagation` | AR Client + DP | Custom timeout → DP receives correct value |\n537: | 11 | `test_ci_run_code_python_writes_and_executes` | CI Client + DP | run_code(\"python\", ...) → write_file + execute_command |\n538: | 12 | `test_ci_run_code_unsupported_language` | CI Client | run_code(\"ruby\", ...) → ValueError |\n539: | 13 | `test_ci_file_operations_delegation` | CI Client + DP | write/upload/download/list all delegate to DP |\n540: | 14 | `test_cp_create_and_delete_session_flow` | CP Client | create_session → delete_session → verify URLs and methods |\n541: | 15 | `test_dp_execute_command_exit_code_error` | CI DP Client | Non-zero exit → CommandExecutionError raised |\n542: | 16 | `test_env_var_precedence_router_url` | CI Client | Arg takes precedence over ROUTER_URL env var |\n543: | 17 | `test_env_var_precedence_workload_manager_url` | CP Client | Arg takes precedence over WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var |\n544: | 18 | `test_ci_stop_idempotent` | CI Client | Multiple stop() calls → each cleanup action called exactly once |\n545: | 19 | `test_ar_close_idempotent` | AR Client | Multiple close() calls → dp_client.close called each time |\n546: | 20 | `test_ci_session_created_flag_behavior` | CI Client | _session_created=True → cleanup on DP failure; False → no cleanup |\n547: \n548: ### 5.4 Mocking Strategy\n549: \n550: | Dependency | Mock Approach | Rationale |\n551: |-----------|---------------|-----------|\n552: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.ControlPlaneClient\")` | Isolates CI client from control plane |\n553: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\")` | Isolates CI client from data plane |\n554: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\")` | Isolates AR client from data plane |\n555: | `requests.Session` methods | `client.session.post = MagicMock(...)` | Direct method replacement on session instance |\n556: | `read_token_from_file` | `patch(\"agentcube.clients.control_plane.read_token_from_file\")` | Avoids filesystem dependency |\n557: | `os.environ` | `patch.dict(os.environ, {...}, clear=True)` | Environment isolation |\n558: | `SA_TOKEN_PATH` | `patch(\"agentcube.clients.control_plane.SA_TOKEN_PATH\", \"/tmp/token\")` | Redirect SA token path |\n559: \n560: ### 5.5 Test Execution\n561: \n562: ```bash\n563: # Run all Python SDK tests\n564: cd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/ -v\n565: \n566: # Run with coverage\n567: cd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/ -v --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing\n568: \n569: # Run specific test file\n570: cd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py -v\n571: \n572: # Run specific test class\n573: cd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestStop -v\n574: \n575: # Run only the newly added tests (by keyword)\n576: cd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_stop_when_session\"\n577: ```\n578: \n579: ### 5.6 Coverage Targets\n580: \n581: | Module | Current (est.) | Target |\n582: |--------|---------------|--------|\n583: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | ~75% (3 stop tests not running) | >95% |\n584: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | ~90% | >95% |\n585: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | ~85% | >95% |\n586: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | ~85% | >95% |\n587: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | ~85% | >95% |\n588: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | ~95% | 100% |\n589: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | ~90% | 100% |\n590: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | ~80% | 100% |\n591: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | ~70% | >90% |\n592: | **Overall** | ~82% | >92% |\n593: \n594: ### 5.7 Risk Areas\n595: \n596: | Risk | Mitigation |\n597: |------|-----------|\n598: | `stop()` methods missing `test_` prefix | Fix immediately — 3 tests silently skipped |\n599: | `close()` idempotency on `requests.Session` | `Session.close()` is safe to call multiple times; tests verify call count |\n600: | Environment variable leakage between tests | Use `patch.dict(os.environ, ..., clear=True)` consistently |\n601: | Logger handler duplication across tests | `get_logger` checks `if not logger.handlers`; test verifies this |\n602: | Base64 encoding edge cases (empty, unicode) | Test with `\"\"`, unicode strings, binary-like content |\n603: | Timeout buffer logic (`+2.0`) | Test with various timeout values to verify buffer applied correctly |\n604: | `urljoin` behavior with trailing slashes | Test both with and without trailing slash on router_url |\n605: \n606: ### 5.8 CI Integration\n607: \n608: The existing CI workflow (`.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml`) runs:\n609: ```yaml\n610: python -m pytest tests/ -v\n611: ```\n612: \n613: No changes needed to CI config. New tests will be picked up automatically by pytest discovery.\n614: \n615: Lint workflow (`.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`) uses `ruff` — ensure new test files pass lint:\n616: ```bash\n617: python3 -m ruff check python-sdk/tests/ --config pyproject.toml\n618: ```\n\n(End of file - total 618 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 单元测试 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers comprehensive Python unit tests for the `agentcube-sdk` package (`sdk-python/`). The SDK provides high-level Python clients for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads.\n\n### 1.2 Scope\n\n| Module | File | Lines | Test File | Status |\n|--------|------|-------|-----------|--------|\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` | 161 | `tests/test_code_interpreter.py` | **Partial** — 635 lines, but 3 methods missing `test_` prefix (won't run) |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` | 79 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** — 837 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` | 96 | `tests/test_control_plane.py` | **Good** — 370 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | 176 | `tests/test_data_plane.py` | **Good** — 641 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | 80 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes | 21 | `tests/test_exceptions.py` | **Good** — 77 lines |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` | 14 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Good** |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` | 7 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Partial** — missing edge cases |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775893340972,"end":1775893340977}}}}
